helptext.en:
Age undetermined – Check the box if the age of the fossil could not be determined.

Minimum time - Select the youngest age for the fossil.

Minimum time uncertain - Check the box if you are unsure of the age assignment.

Maximum time - Select the oldest age for the fossil.

Maximum time uncertain - Check the box if you are unsure of the age assignment.

Geological Group or Lithodemic/Lithotectonic Grouping – Select unit from which fossil was sampled:

  • Stratigraphic Group (or Supergroup) or
  • Lithodemic grouping such as a Complex or
  • Lithotectonic grouping such as an Assemblage

Geological Group Uncertain - Check the box if you are unsure of the Group or Grouping term.

Geological Formation – Select the stratigraphic Formation (or equivalent term) from which the fossil was sampled.

Geological Formation Uncertain – Check the box if you are unsure of the Formation.

Geological Member – Select the stratigraphic Member from which the fossil was sampled.

Geological Member Uncertain - Check the box if you are unsure of the Member.

Informal Map Unit or Name – If formal stratigraphic rank names (group, formation, member) do not apply to the rocks sampled, select an informal stratigraphic name or map unit name from which the fossil was sampled.

Other Informal/Other Unit Name – Enter the informal rock unit name or map unit name (or code) if the unit is not found within the existing picklists.
